
[1]sward

   SWARD, n.

   1. The skin of bacon. [Local.]

   2. The grassy surface of land; turf; that part of the soil which is
   filled with the roots of grass, forming a kind of mat. When covered
   with green grass, it is called green sward.

             SWARD, v.t. To produce sward; to cover with sward.
